timeline.bodyText:
The new sorted and matches change QueryOptions into a mutable class.
One ~easy solution would be to have these generate clones, that "patch" the field of interest.
e.g.
    public QueryOptions sorted(@NonNull final QuerySortBy... sortBy) {
        return new QueryOptions(queryPredicate, paginationInput, Immutable.of(Arrays.asList(sortBy)));
    }
Also, it would certainly be cool* if we could build up the list of QuerySortBy through subsequent appended calls:
Where.sorted(User.LAST_NAME.ascending())
    .sorted(User.FIRST_NAME.ascending())
    .sorted(User.CREATED_AT.descending())
If we were to support that, I guess the impl of this method would be more like:
    public QueryOptions sorted(@NonNull final QuerySortBy... sortBy) {
        List<QuerySortBy> augmentedList = new ArrayList<>(this.sortBy);
        augmentedList.addAll(Immutable.of(sortBy));
        return new QueryOptions(queryPredicate, paginationInput, Immutable.of(augmentedList));
    }

